Package: ICCI
Title: Calculates the Charlson Comorbidity Index
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Kira E.", "Detrois", , "kira.detrois@helsinki.fi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7193-624X"))
Description: Calculates the Charlson Comorbidity Index on longitudinal data in INTERVENE Format. The data should have at least the columns, `ID` and `primary_ICD`, and `ICD_version`. If you want to restrict the exposure period to calculate the index on the data needs an additional column `Event_age`. The package can handle different ICD-versions for the same individual. Possible entries for the column `ICD_version` are "10", "10CM", "9", or "9CM".
